.TH MORE(1),User Commands,MORE(1)

.SH NAME
more - view a file one screen at a time

.SH SYNOPSIS
more [-h] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
more displays file one screenful at a time.
After each full screen it prints a --More-- prompt and waits for a keystroke.
If no file is given, more reads from standard input.

If standard input is not a keyboard (for example, when more is at the end of a pipeline), more prints the entire input without pausing.

The cx16os less(1) is the same program as more and accepts the same keys.

.SH KEYS
space, f, PgDn: advance one full page

Enter, cursor-down: advance one line

q: quit

.SH OPTIONS
-h: Print a short usage summary and exit 0.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
more: unknown option -- X - an unrecognised flag was given.

more: FILE: No such file exists - the named file could not be opened.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: File displayed to completion, or quit requested.

1: The specified file could not be opened, or an unknown option was given.

.SH SEE ALSO
less(1)
